trailingComments.value:
* * Dynamically extends {@link Store} and instantiates the new class. * * `options.getInitialState` and either `options.reducer` or `options.reducers` are required.
* When both are defined, `options.reducers` takes precedence.
* Type requirements are interchangable, meaning either can * take {@link Object} or {@link function}. * @example * let counter = createStore({ * getInitialState() { return 0 }, * reducers: { * inc(state) { return ++state }, * dec(state) { return --state } * } * }) * @param {Object} options * @param {function(): Any} options.getInitialState * @param {function(state: Any, message: Message): Any} options.reducer * @param {Object} options.reducers - maps {@link Message}#type to reducers * @returns {Store}
